d at a protocol level, not a company. Solving for the problem of it being a company however,&#8221; <\/span><\/i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">would mean Elon Musk being the Twitter overlord. He went on to say <\/span><i><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">&#8220;taking it back from Wall Street is the correct first step.&#8221;<\/span><\/i><\/p>\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\" data-dnt=\"true\">\n<p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">Elon\u2019s goal of creating a platform that is \u201cmaximally trusted and broadly inclusive\u201d is the right one. This is also <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/paraga?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">@paraga<\/a>\u2019s goal, and why I chose him. Thank you both for getting the company out of an impossible situation. This is the right path&#8230;I believe it with all my heart.<\/p>\n<p>&mdash; jack<img src=\"https:\/\/www.newsdgtl.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/26a1.png\" alt=\"\u26a1\" class=\"wp-smiley\" style=\"height: 1em;max-height: 1em\" \/> (@jack) <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/jack\/status\/1518772757340639232?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">April 26, 2022<\/a><\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400\">Dorsey&#8217;s remark comes after a day of Twitterverse agony over the repercussions of a wealthy, loud billionaire taking control of <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/elon-musks-tweet-contains-a-covert-message-about-doge\/\">Twitter<\/a>. This real discussion could have ramifications for cryptocurrencies, as <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/twitter-could-accept-elon-musks-offer-within-the-week\/\">Elon Musk<\/a> has made his preference for <a rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https:\/\/crypto-academy.org\/dogecoin-price-increases-in-response-to-the-twitter-offer-by-the-dogefather\/\">Dogecoin (DOGE)<\/a> paym